A devastating 7.8 magnitude earthquake hit Sichuan province, China, causing over 8,700 deaths.
President Dmitry Medvedev offered condolences and assistance to President Hu Jintao.
Despite no warning signs, China allocated 200 million yuan for relief efforts.
The disaster area faces heavy rainfall, hindering relief work and increasing landslide risks.
International support poured in, with Germany and Norway providing financial aid.
Belgium also pledged assistance.
The State Ethnic Affairs Commission granted funds to aid affected ethnic minorities.
The world expresses sympathy and hopes for a swift recovery for those impacted by the tragic event.
